<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="509" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1242,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1279,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs, 2021" authorityName="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[582,673,1280,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[582,673,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. petrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[678,766,1279,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[678,766,1279,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, separated from the other two specie 
<emphasis box="[1172,1360,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
s 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vollenhoven" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[1188,1360,1279,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromedarius">B. dromedarius</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs, 2021" authorityName="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. davidii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[235,324,1315,1341]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[235,324,1315,1341]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the absence of the pointed tubercle on lateral mandibular plates. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs, 2021" authorityName="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[1223,1314,1316,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1223,1314,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. petrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1320,1408,1315,1341]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1320,1408,1315,1341]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the presence of a well developed central tubercle on anterior half of pronotum, which is distinctly longer than width at the base of tubercle; the apex of central tubercle on anterior half of pronotum nearly truncate; the central margin connecting base of central tubercle (anteriomedial tubercle) of scutellum with posteromedial tubercle, C-shaped in lateral view; the pygophore with the caudal angles developed into long, stout horn-like processes, divergent each other; the paramere L-shaped, apex of crown as long as broad, round and clubbed at apex with concave depression on innerside and a dense tuft of setae, projected caudad at the base of the depression; stem of uniform width throughout (
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[201,431,1567,1593]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[308,365,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[442,604,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Figs. 3 C &amp; D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1242,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1603,1629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Genital capsule subquadrangular, caudal angles developed into long, stout horn-like processes, apically slightly divergent from each other. Ventral rim deep, concave, broadly U-shaped. Paramere with single, straight arm, crown broad, slightly L-shaped, round and clubbed at apex. Dense tuft of setae at the innerside of the joint between arm and crown (
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[492,722,1711,1738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[599,655,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="510" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1242,2026]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="510" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1747,1773]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[323,570,1747,1774]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[430,487,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
(1996)
</bibRefCitation>
dealt with two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Rider" authorityYear="2006" box="[870,1056,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[870,1056,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Brachycerocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
namely 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1280,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[1155,1280,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vollenhoven" baseAuthorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromedarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. dromedarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The second author had an opportunity to examine the single female specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1326,1783,1809]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1326,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in David Rider’s laboratory and could clearly associate it with the habitus images and morphological description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[151,394,1855,1882]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[256,313,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
(1996)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[441,571,1855,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[441,571,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[853,976,1855,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[853,976,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not dissected out by considering the comparatively less significance of it in species determination and also to avoid the destruction of the single available specimen; whereas the availability of enough materials of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vollenhoven" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[883,1059,1927,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromedarius">
<emphasis box="[883,1059,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">B. dromedarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the personal collection of the second author [MRC] facilitated the authors to dissect out and study the post abdominal structures of this species besides comparing the external morphology of it with the description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[1031,1275,1999,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[1136,1185,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">et al</emphasis>
. (1996)
</bibRefCitation>
. Based on this study the authors could understand that the figures (
<figureCitation box="[744,896,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Fig. 3.A &amp; B</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W. &amp; O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H." box="[936,1166,151,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" pagination="203 - 212" refId="ref12893" refString="Schaefer, C. W., O'Donnell, J. E. &amp; Patton, J. H. (1996) A review of the Asian species of Brachycerocoris Costa (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae). Oriental Insects, 30 (1), 203 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433842" type="journal article" year="1996">
Schaefer 
<emphasis box="[1043,1093,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
) labelled as 
<taxonomicName box="[1312,1436,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually correspond to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vollenhoven" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[406,579,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromedarius">
<emphasis box="[406,579,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. dromedarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other (
<figureCitation box="[747,894,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Fig. 3.C &amp; D</figureCitation>
of 
