<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1196,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,480,1232,1258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Distributional remarks.</emphasis>
The general external morphology of 
<taxonomicName box="[884,1005,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camelus">
<emphasis box="[884,1005,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. camelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityName="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[1057,1432,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1057,1147,1233,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. petrii</emphasis>
Salini and Roca-Cusachs
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,240,1268,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble each other in general external morphology and can lead to erroneous identification unless the fine details of the external morphology and of male genitalia are closely examined. Therefore, the records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1379,1437,1304,1330]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[200,311,1340,1366]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
probably correspond to the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityName="Salini and Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[720,1106,1340,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[720,813,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">B. petrii</emphasis>
Salini and Roca-Cusachs
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1118,1209,1340,1366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1118,1204,1340,1366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, though the records need verification. This is because an effort to study the post abdominal structures of the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Rider" authorityYear="2006" box="[1251,1437,1376,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1437,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">Brachycerocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available from those regions was never attempted. It is also evident from the differences pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer, C. W." pageId="3" pageNumber="510" pagination="204" refId="ref12852" refString="Schaefer, C. W. (1997) Brachycerocoris camelus Costa (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae: Podopinae) in India: New country record. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 99 (1), 204." type="journal article" year="1997">Schaefer (1997)</bibRefCitation>
among the specimens collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[644,702,1448,1474]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[754,821,1448,1474]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="510">China</collectingCountry>
with respect to the length and height of medial tubercle on pronotum and scutellum and the shape of tubercle between eyes.
</paragraph>
